Web Server:
A computer running web server software that listens for web page requests on TCP port 80.   Examples Apache, IIS (Free with Windows XP onward)

What happen when we type a URL
●	upon entering this URL into the browser, it would: 	
○	ask the DNS server for the IP address of www.aw-bc.com
○	connect to that IP address at port 80
○	ask the server for response
○	display the resulting page on the screenWeb programming technologies

CSS
Describe the appearance, layout, and presentation of information on a web page (as opposed to HTML, which describes the content of the page)

can be embedded in HTML document or placed into separate .css file 	
●	advantage of .css file: one style sheet can be shared across many HTML documents

Inline CSS  
<html>
  <body>
  <h1 style={background-color:red}>  This is Inline CSS </h1>
  </body>
</html>


Embedded (Usually put in header)
selector {
    property: value;
    property: value;
    ...
    property: value;
}

p {
    font-family: sans-serif;
    color: red;
}

A selector can be 1) An element 
                             2) An ID 
                             3) A Class




A Complete CSS example
<!-- An element selector -->
<html>
  <head>
	<style type="text/css">
 	body {
   	   background-color:red;
 	}
	</style>
  </head>
  <body>
   The background color is set using embedded CSS
  </body>
</html>


<!-- A Class selector -->
<html>
  <head>
	<style type="text/css">
  	p.special {
   	  background-color: yellow;
   	  font-weight: bold;
  	}
	</style>
  </head>

  <body>
   <p class=special>The background color is set using embedded CSS </p>
  </body>
</html>



<!-- ID selector-->
<html>
 <head>
	<style type="text/css">

            #missionstatement {
	     font-style: italic;
  	     font-family: serif;
                font-size:400%
          }
</style>
</head>

<body>
<p>TEST</p>
<p id="missionstatement">
THIS IS THE MISSION STATEMENT
</p>
</body>
</html>

External
<link rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" href="style.css" />
style.css is loaded only once and cached by the browser.


Read and practice examples given on following link
http://www.w3schools.com/css/css_syntax.asp
